Our Privacy Policy explains how we collect and use your personal data to determine which advertisements may be relevant to you, and provide other services described below. Connect with people and organizations that interest you. Opportunity to express yourself and communicate on topics that are important to you. Search for content, products and services that may interest you. Ensuring the safety, security and integrity of our services, combating malicious behavior and protecting our user community. Using and developing advanced technologies to provide safe and functional services. Research ways to improve the quality of our services. Ensuring consistency and convenience of various Meta Companies Products. Providing access to our services. Other terms and policies that may apply to you Advertising Rules . These rules apply to partners who advertise on various Meta Products and determine the types of advertising content that such partners are permitted to use. Community Standards . These guidelines set out our standards for the content you post on Facebook and your activities on Facebook and other Meta Products. Community Payment Terms . These terms apply to payments made to or through the Meta Products. Commercial terms . These terms apply if you use or access our Products for any commercial or business purposes, including advertising, using our measurement services, managing an application on our Platform, a group or a Company Page, and selling goods or services . Trade Rules . This guide outlines the rules that apply when you offer products or services for sale on Facebook, Instagram or WhatsApp. Last revision date: July 26, 2023 Data control Account security Privacy Policy What is the Privacy Policy and what does it cover? The main thing in the section At Meta, we want you to understand what information we collect, how we use it, and with whom we use it. let's share. In the Privacy Policy, we explain how we collect, use, store information, and We also share it. We also tell you about your rights. Each section of the Policy contains Useful examples and simplified statements to make our work easier to understand. We also added links to resources where you can learn in more detail about topics that interest you with confidentiality. It is important to us that you know how to manage your privacy (confidentiality), so we also We show you where in the settings of the Meta Products you use you can manage your data. You you can update these settings to personalize your user experience. Полный текст политики приведен ниже. What products are covered by this policy? Learn more about managing your privacy at Privacy Center What information do we collect? The information we collect and process about you depends on how you use our Products . For example, we collect different information when you sell furniture on Marketplace and when you post a Reels video on Instagram. We collect data about you when you use our Products, even if you do not have an account . The following are the types of data we collect: Your actions and information you provide to us Friends, subscribers and other contacts Application, browser and device information Information from Partners, suppliers and other third parties What happens if you do not allow us to collect certain types of information? Some information is necessary for the operation of our Products. Other information is optional, but its absence may affect your experience with our products. More details > What if the information we collect does not personally identify individuals?
